{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, we propose XParaCon (Cross-Paraphrase Consistency):",
    "ST D = StdDev(acc(q i,0), acc(q i,1), acc(q i,2))",
    "where n is the total number of data examples, and acc(q i,j) is the LLM's accuracy on question q j of the ith data example.",
    "This study employs reasoning-based, paraphraseaware Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT) to align models toward semantic invariance across paraphrased questions.",
    "During SFT, each training instance includes both the original question and a paraphrased variant, and the instruction explicitly requires the model to restate the question in its own words, produce a meaning-preserving paraphrase, and verify that the same option is predicted under that paraphrase foot_5."
  ]
}